# Premium iOS UI Foundation

- Use shared design tokens first (`DeviceLayout`, `AppTheme`, `BrandCard`) and avoid one-off magic numbers.
- Keep top-level screen rhythm consistent with `DeviceLayout.sectionSpacing`.
- Use `BrandCard` (or matching overlays/shadows) for elevated surfaces; avoid mixing flat and elevated cards on the same screen.
- Keep content rails consistent: center content, honor `DeviceLayout.contentMaxWidth`, and use shared horizontal padding.
- Prefer clear hierarchy per card: title, supporting info, then actions.

## Quick Pattern

```swift
VStack(alignment: .leading, spacing: DeviceLayout.sectionSpacing) {
    AppBrandedHeader(sectionTitle: "Section", sectionSubtitle: "Context")
    BrandCard { /* content */ }
}
.frame(maxWidth: DeviceLayout.contentMaxWidth, alignment: .leading)
.padding(.horizontal, DeviceLayout.horizontalPadding)
```
